## Resolved mutable: supervisor-acquire-single-instance-toctou-race

FIXED the TOCTOU race in acquireSingleInstance in BOTH gm-plugkit/supervisor.js and bin/plugkit-supervisor.js: replaced the non-atomic existsSync->read->write with an atomic O_EXCL exclusive-create (fs.openSync(SUPERVISOR_PID_PATH, wx)). Now when N supervisors race to start in the same instant, openSync wx succeeds for exactly ONE (the file create is atomic); the rest get EEXIST -> read holder -> if alive refuse+exit, if dead/stale unlink+retry-once. This neutralizes the concurrent-burst duplicate-spawn the plain check-then-write let through (witnessed: 4 supervisor.starting at 12:39:11 with zero refused-duplicate). node --check passes both. The bootstrap spawning a burst of supervisors per skill-load is now harmless (the guard rejects all but one). Ships via gm-skill (bin) + gm-plugkit publish.